name: Level Six Twelve Six Touring V2 SUP
description: Pull off more forward strokes as you paddle for fitness or explore new coastlines. The displacement hull is a good size for paddlers up 230lb. The shape tracks straight and true so you make fewer sweeps and faster, smoother progress. This is also a great stock-length board for paddlers looking for a race board with a little extra stability.Multi-layer epoxy and glass construction ensures durability and keeps it looking beautiful.Clear coat finish uses tri-layer fibreglass epoxy resin.Lightweight EPS foam core with 5-layer reinforced sidewalls.Deck pad makes touring days more comfortable.Ergonomic carry handle make the car-to-beach transition easier.Lots of lash points let you carry gear on deck for longer days or overnight missions.Modified race fin has a large surface area to increase lateral stability and improve tracking.Includes fin screw, fin plate and fin key.
